A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Election Law – Voting Age – Board of Education Elections
3 (Your School, Your Voice Act)
4 FOR the purpose of authorizing the General Assembly to provide by suitable enactment the
5 authority of a county to lower the age at which an individual may vote in an election
6 for members of an elected county board of education; authorizing, if authorized by
7 the county in which the individual is registered to vote, an individual under a certain
8 age to vote in an election for members of an elected county board of education;
9 authorizing a county to enact a local law that allows an individual who is at least a
10 certain age to vote in an election for members of an elected county board of education;
11 and generally relating to the age at which an individual may vote in board of
12 education elections.
